  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "By harnessing large datasets from both biological and artificial sources, researchers can uncover nuanced patterns in taste perception that would otherwise remain hidden.",
    "Among these techniques, supervised learning stands out as a particularly influential method in taste analysis (Naciri et al. 2023).",
    "This approach involves training models on labeled datasets to predict outcomes based on specific input features, enabling the recognition of patterns and relationships within the data.",
    "Common algorithms employed include Linear Regression (Iwaniak et al. 2019), which predicts continuous variables such as the sweetness or bitterness of food compounds based on their chemical properties, allowing for quantification of taste attributes.",
    "Additionally, Support Vector Machines (SVM) classify data points into distinct categories, effectively differentiating among various taste profiles (Zeng et al. 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Among these techniques, supervised learning stands out as a particularly influential method in taste analysis (Naciri et al. 2023).",
